response.original_title: Trashcan Sinatras: Midnight At The Troubadour
response.overview: Ccaptures the band's sold-out show at the Troubadour in Los Angeles, on October 4, 2004. Bonus content includes 2 songs and an interview from the band's March 16, 2004 appearance on KCRW's Morning Becomes Eclectic show, as well as 10 songs from the band's sold-out performance at the Troubadour that same night, which was their first concert in California in over 10 years.  Main show: 1. The Sleeping Policeman 2. Freetime 3. Easy Read 4. All The Dark Horses 5. January's Little Joke 6. It's A Miracle 7. Twisted And Bent 8. Got Carried Away 9. The Genius I Was 10. I Must Fly 11. I'm The One Who Fainted 12. Orange Fell 13. The Main Attraction 14. Country Air 15. I'm Immortal 16. Weightligting 17. Welcome Back 18. The Hairy Years 19. The Safecracker
response.title: Trashcan Sinatras: Midnight At The Troubadour
